Mumbai, India355 contributions
Mesmerising beauty
Dec 2019 â€¢ Couples
Truly a piece of Heaven on earth. Hundreds of limestone islands(actually 1969 according to locals) dotting a tranquil bay. Ignore everything you read about crowds of boats, polluted water and all - the beauty of this place overpowers everything.
Make sure you take a one night cruise; a day cruise is too rushed. If you book through your hotel you pay higher, but it is worth saving the hassle. You are on a holiday to enjoy, after all.
The cruises try to pack your time with activities - most on-board activities like cooking classes, tai chi etc can be given a miss. Use that time on the sundeck, soaking up the atmosphere and the sunset.
