Trash and oil in the waters - everywhere!!
Apr 2023 â€¢ Family
I had a lot of doubts about our 3 days 2 nights trip to Halong Bay because I saw no ao appealing pictures of hundreds of boats following the same routes. I should have listened to my gut feeling. The landscape is really unique and you wonâ€™t find anything like this anywhere else BUT this mass tourism totally DESTROYS the beauty of this place.
There is visual, acoustic and sensory contamination throughout the whole day. The air is contaminated with motor oil smell (that even enters the cabins of the cruise boats ) and the noises of the cruise engines is unbearable . I was not able to relax even one minute, not even at 6am in the morning. the waters are full of garbage and oil. It was disgusting! So of course we did not go swimming! Even the kayaking through the layers of foam and oil on the surface was horrible.
We were told that apparently the government since 2016 has rolled out a plan to dismantle the floating villages and the garbage are remainders of those but in my opinion this is only an excuse.
Please donâ€™t support this irresponsible mass tourism until the government and cruise companies clean the waters and protect this beauty! As long as so many people flock in and pay lots of money the companies just see the $ signs and wonâ€™t change anything.
